/**
 * @mainpage Vectra Backend API Documentation
 * 
 * @section overview Overview
 * 
 * Vectra (Geospatial Emergency Evacuation & Network Analysis Platform) is a
 * comprehensive backend system for emergency evacuation routing and network flow
 * analysis using FDOT (Florida Department of Transportation) public data.
 * 
 * @section features Key Features
 * - Road network analysis with 20,401+ segments
 * - PostGIS spatial database integration
 * - Max-flow evacuation simulation (Edmonds-Karp algorithm)
 * - Official FDOT road classification
 * - JSON-driven scenario management
 * - RESTful FastAPI endpoints
 * - Network topology with pgRouting
 * 
 * @section modules Main Modules
 * 
 * @subsection db Database Layer
 * - @ref app.db.base "Base Configuration"
 * - @ref app.db.database "Connection Management"
 * - @ref app.db.seed "Database Initialization"
 * 
 * @subsection models Data Models
 * - @ref app.models.road_network "Road Network Model"
 * 
 * @subsection api API Layer
 * - @ref app.api.routes "Route Handlers"
 * 
 * @subsection etl ETL Pipeline
 * - @ref app.etl.ingest_fdot "FDOT Data Ingestion"
 * 
 * @subsection services Business Logic
 * - @ref app.services.evacuation "Evacuation Service"
 * 
