 * @section getting_started Getting Started
 * 
 * @subsection install Installation
 * @code{.bash}
 * cd backend
 * pip install -r requirements.txt
 * export DATABASE_URL="postgresql://user:pass@localhost/vectra"
 * python -m uvicorn app.main:app --reload
 * @endcode
 * 
 * @subsection api_usage API Usage
 * @code{.bash}
 * # Get road segments
 * curl http://localhost:8000/api/segments
 * 
 * # Run evacuation simulation
 * curl "http://localhost:8000/api/simulate?scenario=contraflow&region=Tampa%20Bay"
 * 
 * # Get hurricane scenarios
 * curl http://localhost:8000/api/hurricane-scenarios
 * @endcode
 * 
 * @section testing Testing
 * @code{.bash}
 * pip install -r requirements-test.txt
 * pytest tests/ -v --cov=app
 * @endcode
 * 
 * @section architecture Architecture
 * 
 * Vectra follows a layered architecture:
 * 
 * @verbatim
 *     API Layer (FastAPI Routes)
 *          ↓
 *     Service Layer (Business Logic)
 *          ↓
 *     Data Access Layer (SQLAlchemy ORM)
 *          ↓
 *     Database Layer (PostGIS)
 * @endverbatim
 * 
 * @section data_flow Data Flow
 * 
 * @verbatim
 *     FDOT Shapefiles
 *            ↓
 *     ETL Pipeline (ingest_fdot.py)
 *            ↓
 *     PostGIS Database
 *            ↓
 *     ORM Models (road_network.py)
 *            ↓
 *     Service Layer (evacuation.py)
 *            ↓
 *     API Endpoints (routes.py)
 *            ↓
 *     JSON Responses (GeoJSON, Metrics)
 * @endverbatim
 * 
 * @section datasets Datasets
 * 
 * All data sources are from FDOT public data:
 * - basemap_route_road.shp: Complete road network (20,401 segments)
 * - interstates/interstates.shp: 72 interstate segments
 * - toll_roads/toll_roads.shp: 81 toll road segments
 * - number_of_lanes.shp: Lane count attributes
 * - maxspeed.shp: Speed limit attributes
 * 
 * @section algorithms Key Algorithms
 * 
 * @subsection maxflow Max Flow Calculation
 * - Algorithm: Edmonds-Karp (Ford-Fulkerson implementation)
 * - Purpose: Calculate maximum evacuation throughput
 * - Complexity: O(V*E²)
 * 
 * @subsection capacity Capacity Calculation
 * - Formula: capacity = lanes × 1800 vph
 * - Standard: HCM (Highway Capacity Manual)
 * 
 * @subsection cost Travel Time
 * - Formula: cost_time = distance (m) / speed (m/s)
 * - Units: Seconds
 * 
 * @section performance Performance
 * 
 * - Road segments processed: 20,401
 * - Network nodes: ~3,500
 * - Network edges: ~6,000
 * - Max flow calculation: <5 seconds
 * - Spatial index: GIST (PostGIS)
 * 
 * @section references References
 * 
 * - FDOT Road Centerline Inventory (RCI)
 * - Highway Capacity Manual 7th Edition (HCM)
 * - Saffir-Simpson Hurricane Wind Scale
 * - pgRouting Network Analysis
 * - NetworkX Graph Algorithms
